[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m66[0m[39m:     *[0m[35m/[0m                                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m67[0m[39m:    public static Type1Font [0m[1;35mcreateWithPFB[0m[1;39m([0m[39mbyte[0m[1;39m[[0m[1;39m][0m[39m pfbBytes[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m throws IOException[0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m68[0m[39m:    [0m[1;39m{[0m                                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m69[0m[39m:        PfbParser pfb = new [0m[1;35mPfbParser[0m[1;39m([0m[39mpfbBytes[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m70[0m[39m:        Type1Parser parser = new [0m[1;35mType1Parser[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m71[0m[39m:        return [0m[1;35mparser.parse[0m[1;39m([0m[1;35mpfb.getSegment1[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m, [0m[1;35mpfb.getSegment2[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m72[0m[39m:    [0m[1;39m}[0m                                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m73[0m[39m:[0m                                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m74[0m[39m:    [0m[35m/[0m[39m**[0m                                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m75[0m[39m:     * Constructs a new Type1Font object from two header-less .pfb segments.[0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m76[0m[39m:     *[0m                                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m77[0m[39m:     * @param segment1 The first segment, without header[0m                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m78[0m[39m:     * @param segment2 The second segment, without header[0m                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m79[0m[39m:     * @return A new Type1Font instance[0m                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m80[0m[39m:     * @throws IOException if something went wrong[0m                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m81[0m[39m:     *[0m[35m/[0m                                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m82[0m[39m:    public static Type1Font [0m[1;35mcreateWithSegments[0m[1;39m([0m[39mbyte[0m[1;39m[[0m[1;39m][0m[39m segment1, byte[0m[1;39m[[0m[1;39m][0m[39m segment2[0m[1;39m)[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mthrows IOException[0m                                                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m83[0m[39m:    [0m[1;39m{[0m                                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m84[0m[39m:        Type1Parser parser = new [0m[1;35mType1Parser[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m85[0m[39m:        return [0m[1;35mparser.parse[0m[1;39m([0m[39msegment1, segment2[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m86[0m[39m:    [0m[1;39m}[0m                                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m87[0m[39m:[0m                                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m88[0m[39m:    [0m[35m/[0m[35m/[0m[39m font dictionary[0m                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m89[0m[39m:    String fontName = [0m[32m""[0m[39m;[0m                                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m90[0m[39m:    Encoding encoding = null;[0m                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m91[0m[39m:    int paintType;[0m                                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m92[0m[39m:    int fontType;[0m                                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m93[0m[39m:    List<Number> fontMatrix = [0m[1;35mCollections.emptyList[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m94[0m[39m:    List<Number> fontBBox = [0m[1;35mCollections.emptyList[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m95[0m[39m:    int uniqueID;[0m                                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m96[0m[39m:    float strokeWidth;[0m                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m97[0m[39m:    String fontID = [0m[32m""[0m[39m;[0m                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m98[0m[39m:[0m                                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m99[0m[39m:    [0m[35m/[0m[35m/[0m[39m FontInfo dictionary[0m                                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m100[0m[39m:    String version = [0m[32m""[0m[39m;[0m                                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m```[0m                                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<[0m[35m/[0m[95mcode[0m[39m>[0m                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<code>[0m                                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mpdfbox/src/main/java/org/apache/pdfbox/pdmodel/font/PDType1Font.jav[0m[1;92ma:200[0m[39m-[0m[1;36m235[0m        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m```[0m                                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m200[0m[39m:            if [0m[1;39m([0m[39mfontFile3 != null[0m[1;39m)[0m                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m201[0m[39m:            [0m[1;39m{[0m                                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m202[0m[39m:                [0m[1;35mLOG.warn[0m[1;39m([0m[32m"/FontFile3 for Type1 font not supported"[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m203[0m[39m:            [0m[1;39m}[0m                                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m204[0m[39m:[0m                                                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m205[0m[39m:            [0m[35m/[0m[35m/[0m[39m or it may contain a PFB[0m                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m206[0m[39m:            PDStream fontFile = [0m[1;35mfd.getFontFile[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m207[0m[39m:            if [0m[1;39m([0m[39mfontFile != null[0m[1;39m)[0m                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m208[0m[39m:            [0m[1;39m{[0m                                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m209[0m[39m:                try[0m                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m210[0m[39m:                [0m[1;39m{[0m                                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m211[0m[39m:                    COSStream stream = [0m[1;35mfontFile.getCOSObject[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m212[0m[39m:                    int length1 = [0m[1;35mstream.getInt[0m[1;39m([0m[39mCOSName.LENGTH1[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m213[0m[39m:                    int length2 = [0m[1;35mstream.getInt[0m[1;39m([0m[39mCOSName.LENGTH2[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m214[0m[39m:[0m                                                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m215[0m[39m:                    [0m[35m/[0m[35m/[0m[39m repair Length1 and Length2 if necessary[0m                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m216[0m[39m:                    byte[0m[1;39m[[0m[1;39m][0m[39m bytes = [0m[1;35mfontFile.toByteArray[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m217[0m[39m:                    if [0m[1;39m([0m[39mbytes.length == [0m[1;36m0[0m[1;39m)[0m                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m218[0m[39m:                    [0m[1;39m{[0m                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m219[0m[39m:                        throw new [0m[1;35mIOException[0m[1;39m([0m[32m"Font data unavailable"[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m220[0m[39m:                    [0m[1;39m}[0m                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m221[0m[39m:                    length1 = [0m[1;35mrepairLength1[0m[1;39m([0m[39mbytes, length1[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m222[0m[39m:                    length2 = [0m[1;35mrepairLength2[0m[1;39m([0m[39mbytes, length1, length2[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m223[0m[39m:[0m                                                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m224[0m[39m:                    if [0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m([0m[39mbytes[0m[1;39m[[0m[1;36m0[0m[1;39m][0m[39m & [0m[1;36m0xff[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m == PFB_START_MARKER[0m[1;39m)[0m                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m225[0m[39m:                    [0m[1;39m{[0m                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m226[0m[39m:                        [0m[35m/[0m[35m/[0m[39m some bad files embed the entire PFB, see PDFBOX-[0m[1;36m2607[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m227[0m[39m:                        t1 = [0m[1;35mType1Font.createWithPFB[0m[1;39m([0m[39mbytes[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m228[0m[39m:                    [0m[1;39m}[0m                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m229[0m[39m:                    else[0m                                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m230[0m[39m:                    [0m[1;39m{[0m                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m231[0m[39m:                        [0m[35m/[0m[35m/[0m[39m the PFB embedded as two segments back-to-back[0m        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m232[0m[39m:                        if [0m[1;39m([0m[39mlength1 < [0m[1;36m0[0m[39m || length1 > length1 + length2[0m[1;39m)[0m         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m233[0m[39m:                        [0m[1;39m{[0m                                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m234[0m[39m:                            throw new [0m[1;35mIOException[0m[1;39m([0m[32m"Invalid length data, actual [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [32mlength: "[0m[39m +[0m                                                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m235[0m[39m:                                    bytes.length + [0m[32m", /Length1: "[0m[39m + length1 + [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [32m", /Length2: "[0m[39m + length2[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m```[0m                                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<[0m[35m/[0m[95mcode[0m[39m>[0m                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<[0m[35m/[0m[95mcode_snippets[0m[39m>[0m                                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## Fix Strategy[0m                                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<fix_strategy>[0m                                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mTo eliminate the persistent libFuzzer timeouts in Type1 font parsing, we must [0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mproactively short-circuit any large or malicious inputs before they enter [0m          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mlong-running loops [0m[1;39m([0m[39mhex-to-binary conversion, decryption, or backward scans[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m. The [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mprevious “large” thresholds [0m[1;39m([0m[1;36m20[0m[39m MB for decryption, [0m[1;36m100[0m[39m MB for PFB[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m are still too [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mgenerous under fuzzing, so we need to:[0m                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1[0m[39m. **Lower and unify size limits.**  [0m                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Define a single, modest maximum [0m[1;39m([0m[39me.g. [0m[1;36m5[0m[39m MB[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m for any raw or decrypted Type [0m[1;36m1[0m[39m [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39msegment.  [0m                                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Expose it as a public constant [0m[1;39m([0m[39me.g. `Type1Parser.MAX_BINARY_SEGMENT_SIZE`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m so[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mall callers can share the same guard.[0m                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m2[0m[39m. **Short-circuit in `[0m[1;35mType1Parser.parseBinary[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m`.**  [0m                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - **At the very top** of `[0m[1;35mparseBinary[0m[1;39m([0m[39mbyte[0m[1;39m[[0m[1;39m][0m[39m bytes[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m`, before any `[0m[1;35misBinary[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m`, [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`[0m[1;35mhexToBinary[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` or `[0m[1;35mdecrypt[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` calls, check  [0m                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m       `if [0m[1;39m([0m[39mbytes.length > MAX_BINARY_SEGMENT_SIZE[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m throw new [0m[1;35mIOException[0m[1;39m([0m[32m"Type1 [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [32msegment too large"[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;`  [0m                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - This halts pathological inputs instantly, avoiding [0m[1;35mO[0m[1;39m([0m[39mn[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m hex-parsing or [0m        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mdecryption loops on multi-megabyte arrays.[0m                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m3[0m[39m. **Pre-guard in `[0m[1;35mType1Font.createWithPFB[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m`.**  [0m                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Before instantiating the parser or calling `[0m[1;35mparseBinary[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m`, inspect the raw [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mPFB “encrypted” segment [0m[1;39m([0m[39msegment [0m[1;36m2[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m. If its length exceeds [0m                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`Type1Parser.MAX_BINARY_SEGMENT_SIZE`, throw an `IOException`.  [0m                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - This prevents even allocating or slicing the segment into byte arrays that [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mwould later be decrypted.[0m                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m4[0m[39m. **Tighten the PFB‐size check in `PDType1Font`.**  [0m                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Reduce the existing [0m[1;36m100[0m[39m MB cap on full PFB data to the same [0m[1;36m5[0m[39m MB threshold, [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mensuring we never enter the subsequent `[0m[1;35mrepairLength1[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m`[0m[35m/[0m[39m`[0m[1;35mrepairLength2[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` scans on[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mhuge buffers.  [0m                                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Place this check **as early as possible** in the constructor or loader [0m        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mroutine, before any backward scans.[0m                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m5[0m[39m. **[0m[1;39m([0m[39mOptional[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m Protect backward‐scan routines.**  [0m                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - In `[0m[1;35mrepairLength1[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` and `[0m[1;35mrepairLength2[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m`, if `bytes.length` still exceeds a [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39msafe upper bound, either bail out immediately or limit the number of backward [0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39miterations [0m[1;39m([0m[39me.g. at most N = [0m[1;36m1[0m[39m [0m[1;36m000[0m[39m [0m[1;36m000[0m[39m bytes scanned[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m.  [0m                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - This is a secondary safeguard to guarantee [0m[1;35mO[0m[1;39m([0m[1;36m1[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m behavior on outliers.[0m          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mWhy this works  [0m                                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m– All heavy loops [0m[1;39m([0m[39mhex decoding, decryption, backward scans[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m are gated behind a [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mcheap length check [0m[1;39m([0m[1;35mO[0m[1;39m([0m[1;36m1[0m[1;39m)[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m.  [0m                                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m– By unifying on a single, relatively low watermark [0m[1;39m([0m[39m≈[0m[1;36m5[0m[39m MB[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m, we guarantee that [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mfuzzing inputs will never trigger pathological [0m[1;35mO[0m[1;39m([0m[39mn[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m work on multi-megabyte data.  [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m– Throwing an `IOException` is consistent with existing code paths [0m[1;39m([0m[39malready [0m        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mcatching parsing errors[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m and allows PDFTextStripper to skip the problematic font [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mgracefully.  [0m                                                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m– We preserve the existing counts and grammar checks [0m[1;39m([0m[39m`[0m[35m/[0m[95mSubrs[0m[39m`, `[0m[35m/[0m[95mCharStrings[0m[39m`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m for[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mwell-formed, small fonts, so normal PDFs remain unaffected.[0m                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mSide effects & mitigation  [0m                                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m– Very large but benign Type [0m[1;36m1[0m[39m fonts [0m[1;39m([0m[39m>[0m[1;36m5[0m[39m MB[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m will now be skipped; clients relying [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mon those may see missing glyphs or warnings. If this upper bound is too low for [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mreal-world usage, the constant can be tuned upward modestly [0m[1;39m([0m[39me.g. to [0m[1;36m10[0m[39m MB[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m without[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mre-introducing the fuzzer hang.  [0m                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m– Because we abort parsing at the first size check, we avoid any risk of catching [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mexcessively broad exceptions later in the parsing logic.  [0m                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m– Existing unit tests for small/standard Type [0m[1;36m1[0m[39m fonts continue to pass unmodified. [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mNo harness or test code changes are required.[0m                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mCode-area references for patching:  [0m                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<code_range>fontbox/src/main/java/org/apache/fontbox/type1/Type1Parser.jav[0m[1;92ma:535[0m[39m-[0m[1;36m550[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<[0m[35m/[0m[95mcode_range[0m[39m>  [0m                                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<code_range>fontbox/src/main/java/org/apache/fontbox/type1/Type1Font.jav[0m[1;92ma:60[0m[39m-[0m[1;36m100[0m[39m<[0m[35m/[0m[95mc[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [95mode_range[0m[39m>  [0m                                                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<code_range>pdfbox/src/main/java/org/apache/pdfbox/pdmodel/font/PDType1Font.jav[0m[1;92ma:20[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;92m0[0m[39m-[0m[1;36m235[0m[39m<[0m[35m/[0m[95mcode_range[0m[39m>[0m                                                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<[0m[35m/[0m[95mfix_strategy[0m[1m>[0m                                                                     [2m                [0m

[2;36m                    [0m         [39m# Evaluation Report[0m                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## Summary[0m                                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mThe fuzzer run against PDFBox/FontBox hung on a `libFuzzer: timeout` while [0m         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mprocessing a Type [0m[1;36m1[0m[39m font. The hang occurred during `Type1Parser.parseBinary`, which[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mwas spending excessive time in hex-to-binary conversion and decryption loops on [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mlarge inputs.[0m                                                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mAn attempted patch introduced a `MAX_BINARY_SEGMENT_SIZE` constant in `Type1Parser`[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mand added pre-checks in:[0m                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- `[0m[1;35mType1Parser.parseBinary[0m[1;39m([0m[39mbyte[0m[1;39m[[0m[1;39m][0m[1;39m)[0m[39m`[0m                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- `[0m[1;35mType1Font.createWithPFB[0m[1;39m([0m[39mbyte[0m[1;39m[[0m[1;39m][0m[1;39m)[0m[39m`[0m                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- `PDType1Font`’s embedded-font loader[0m                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mThese checks were intended to reject segments larger than [0m[1;36m5[0m[39m [0m[1;36m000[0m[39m [0m[1;36m000[0m[39m bytes early. [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mAfter applying the patch, PDFBox failed to compile because `Type1Parser` is [0m        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mpackage-private in FontBox and cannot be referenced from the PDFBox module [0m         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;39m([0m[39m`PDType1Font`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m.[0m                                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## Description[0m                                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1[0m[39m. Initial Issue  [0m                                                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - A `libFuzzer` run timed out after ~[0m[1;36m27[0m[39m seconds.  [0m                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Thread dump shows the main thread stuck in:[0m                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     ```[0m                                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     [0m[1;35mcom.code_intelligence.jazzer.runtime.TraceDataFlowNativeCallbacks.traceConstCm[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;35mpInt[0m[1;39m([0m[39mNative Method[0m[1;39m)[0m                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     at [0m[1;35morg.apache.fontbox.type1.Type1Parser.parseBinary[0m[1;39m([0m[39mType1Parser.jav[0m[1;92ma:640[0m[1;39m)[0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     ```[0m                                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - The parser was handling a large or maliciously crafted Type [0m[1;36m1[0m[39m binary segment, [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mtriggering expensive hex conversion or decryption loops.[0m                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - No exceptions were thrown; the parser simply spent too much CPU time on the [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39msegment.[0m                                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m2[0m[39m. Patch Attempt  [0m                                                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - In FontBox’s `Type1Parser` [0m                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;39m([0m[39msrc/main/java/org/apache/fontbox/type1/Type1Parser.java[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m:[0m                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     • Added `public static final int MAX_BINARY_SEGMENT_SIZE = 5_000_000;`  [0m       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     • At the start of `[0m[1;35mparseBinary[0m[1;39m([0m[39mbyte[0m[1;39m[[0m[1;39m][0m[39m bytes[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m`, added:[0m                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m       ```[0m                                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m       if [0m[1;39m([0m[39mbytes.length > MAX_BINARY_SEGMENT_SIZE[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m[1;39m{[0m                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m           throw new [0m[1;35mIOException[0m[1;39m([0m[32m"Type1 binary segment too large [0m[32m([0m[32m"[0m[39m + bytes.length [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m+ [0m[32m" bytes[0m[32m)[0m[32m"[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                                                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m       [0m[1;39m}[0m                                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m       ```[0m                                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - In FontBox’s `Type1Font` [0m                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;39m([0m[39msrc/main/java/org/apache/fontbox/type1/Type1Font.java[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m:[0m                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     • Before calling the parser, checked `seg2.length` against [0m                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`MAX_BINARY_SEGMENT_SIZE` and threw `IOException` if exceeded.[0m                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - In PDFBox’s `PDType1Font` [0m                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;39m([0m[39msrc/main/java/org/apache/pdfbox/pdmodel/font/PDType1Font.java[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m:[0m                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     • Before repairing lengths of an embedded PFB, checked `bytes.length` against [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`Type1Parser.MAX_BINARY_SEGMENT_SIZE` and threw `IOException` if too large.[0m         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m3[0m[39m. Patch Application Result  [0m                                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - FontBox module compiled successfully with the new constant and checks.  [0m       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - PDFBox module failed to compile with:[0m                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     ```[0m                                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     org.apache.fontbox.type1.Type1Parser is not public in [0m                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39morg.apache.fontbox.type1; cannot be accessed from outside package[0m                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     ```[0m                                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - The failure occurs because `Type1Parser` is package-private, so its [0m           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`MAX_BINARY_SEGMENT_SIZE` cannot be referenced from the PDFBox code.[0m                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m4[0m[39m. Areas for Further Investigation  [0m                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Visibility and API boundaries between FontBox and PDFBox:  [0m                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     • The intended constant is declared in a non-public class.  [0m                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     • PDFBox requires either a public accessor or relocation of the constant.  [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - All font-parsing entry points that accept raw or decrypted data segments, [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mincluding:  [0m                                                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     • `Type1Parser`’s handling of hex vs. binary sections.  [0m                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     • `PfbParser` segments [0m[1;36m1[0m[39m and [0m[1;36m2[0m[39m sizes.  [0m                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     • PDFBox’s embedded-font loader paths beyond `PDType1Font`.  [0m                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Any other parse methods [0m[1;39m([0m[39me.g., CID, CFF[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m that may perform similar loops on [0m    [2m                [0m

[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<fix_strategy>[0m                                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1[0m[39m. Relocate the segment‐size constant into FontBox’s public API  [0m                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   a. In Type1Font [0m[1;39m([0m[39mpublic class[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m, add at the top:[0m                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      ```[0m                                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      [0m[35m/[0m[39m** Maximum allowed size for any raw or decrypted Type1 binary segment [0m[1;39m([0m[1;36m5[0m[39m [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mMB[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m. *[0m[35m/[0m                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      public static final int MAX_BINARY_SEGMENT_SIZE = 5_000_000;[0m                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      ```  [0m                                                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   b. Remove `public static final int MAX_BINARY_SEGMENT_SIZE` from the [0m            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mpackage-private Type1Parser.  [0m                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   c. In Type1Parser.parseBinary, replace the self-declared guard with:[0m             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      ```[0m                                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      if [0m[1;39m([0m[39mbytes.length > Type1Font.MAX_BINARY_SEGMENT_SIZE[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m[1;39m{[0m                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m          throw new [0m[1;35mIOException[0m[1;39m([0m[32m"Type1 binary segment too large [0m[32m([0m[32m"[0m[39m + bytes.length +[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [32m" bytes[0m[32m)[0m[32m"[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                                                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      [0m[1;39m}[0m                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      ```[0m                                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      [0m[1;39m([0m[39mImport org.apache.fontbox.type1.Type1Font.[0m[1;39m)[0m                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m2[0m[39m. Enforce early checks in FontBox’s public factory methods  [0m                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   a. In `[0m[1;35mType1Font.createWithPFB[0m[1;39m([0m[39mInputStream[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` and `[0m[1;35m.createWithPFB[0m[1;39m([0m[39mbyte[0m[1;39m[[0m[1;39m][0m[1;39m)[0m[39m`, [0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mbefore invoking PfbParser:[0m                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      - Check the raw stream/byte[0m[1;39m[[0m[1;39m][0m[39m length against MAX_BINARY_SEGMENT_SIZE; throw [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mIOException if exceeded.  [0m                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      - After parsing into segments, additionally guard segment2 [0m[1;39m([0m[39mencrypted data[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mlength:[0m                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m        ```[0m                                                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m        if [0m[1;39m([0m[39mseg2.length > MAX_BINARY_SEGMENT_SIZE[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m[1;39m{[0m                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m            throw new [0m[1;35mIOException[0m[1;39m([0m[32m"Type1 segment too large [0m[32m([0m[32m"[0m[39m + seg2.length + [0m[32m" [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [32mbytes[0m[32m)[0m[32m"[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m        [0m[1;39m}[0m                                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m        ```[0m                                                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   b. In `[0m[1;35mType1Font.createWithSegments[0m[1;39m([0m[39mbyte[0m[1;39m[[0m[1;39m][0m[39m segment1, byte[0m[1;39m[[0m[1;39m][0m[39m segment2[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m`, at the [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mtop:[0m                                                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      ```[0m                                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      if [0m[1;39m([0m[39msegment1.length > MAX_BINARY_SEGMENT_SIZE[0m                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m          || segment2.length > MAX_BINARY_SEGMENT_SIZE[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m[1;39m{[0m                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m          throw new [0m[1;35mIOException[0m[1;39m([0m[32m"Type1 segments too large: "[0m                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m                                 + segment1.length + [0m[32m", "[0m[39m + segment2.length[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      [0m[1;39m}[0m                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      ```[0m                                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   This centralizes all size guards in the public API, so any consumer can [0m         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mreference a single constant.[0m                                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m3[0m[39m. Update PDFBox to use the public constant and add its own pre‐checks  [0m            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   a. Remove references to `Type1Parser.MAX_BINARY_SEGMENT_SIZE`; import [0m           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`org.apache.fontbox.type1.Type1Font`.  [0m                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   b. In `PDType1Font`’s embedded‐PFB loader:[0m                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      - Before repairing lengths [0m[1;39m([0m[39m`repairLength1/[0m[1;36m2[0m[39m`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m, check `bytes.length`:[0m         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m        ```[0m                                                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m        if [0m[1;39m([0m[39mbytes.length > Type1Font.MAX_BINARY_SEGMENT_SIZE[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m[1;39m{[0m                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m            throw new [0m[1;35mIOException[0m[1;39m([0m[32m"Embedded PFB too large: "[0m[39m + bytes.length[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m        [0m[1;39m}[0m                                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m        ```[0m                                                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      - In the PFB‐start branch, before `[0m[1;35mType1Font.createWithPFB[0m[1;39m([0m[39mbytes[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m`:[0m           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m        ```[0m                                                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m        [0m[35m/[0m[35m/[0m[39m guard huge embedded PFB[0m                                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m        if [0m[1;39m([0m[39mbytes.length > Type1Font.MAX_BINARY_SEGMENT_SIZE[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m[1;39m{[0m                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m            throw new [0m[1;35mIOException[0m[1;39m([0m[32m"Embedded PFB too large: "[0m[39m + bytes.length[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m        [0m[1;39m}[0m                                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m        ```[0m                                                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      - In the two‐segment branch, after extracting `segment1`[0m[35m/[0m[39m`segment2`, guard [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39meach:[0m                                                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m        ```[0m                                                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m        if [0m[1;39m([0m[39msegment1.length > Type1Font.MAX_BINARY_SEGMENT_SIZE[0m                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m            || segment2.length > Type1Font.MAX_BINARY_SEGMENT_SIZE[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m[1;39m{[0m               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m            throw new [0m[1;35mIOException[0m[1;39m([0m[32m"Embedded Type1 segments too large: "[0m             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m                                   + segment1.length + [0m[32m", "[0m[39m + segment2.length[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m        [0m[1;39m}[0m                                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m        ```[0m                                                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m4[0m[39m. Rationale and preservation of functionality  [0m                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - By placing the constant in Type1Font [0m[1;39m([0m[39mpublic[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m, both FontBox internals and [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mPDFBox consumers share a single API point; no need to expose or re-publish [0m         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mpackage‐private Type1Parser.  [0m                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Early checks in public factory methods and in PDType1Font stop oversized data [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mbefore hex‐to‐binary conversion and decryption loops, preventing fuzzer timeouts.  [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Existing parsing logic, return values, and exception types remain unchanged [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mfor normal‐sized fonts, ensuring backward compatibility.  [0m                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Error messages remain descriptive, aiding debugging of genuine large‐font [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39merrors.  [0m                                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m5[0m[39m. Mitigations and side effects  [0m                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Legitimate fonts larger than [0m[1;36m5[0m[39m MB will now be rejected; if this is too [0m        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mrestrictive for some use cases, raise `MAX_BINARY_SEGMENT_SIZE` or make it [0m         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mconfigurable.  [0m                                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Ensure no other code references the old constant in Type1Parser; all size [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mchecks must centralize to Type1Font.  [0m                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Run the full FontBox/PDFBox test suite to verify no regressions.  [0m             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m6[0m[39m. Relevant code ranges for patch context  [0m                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   <code_range>fontbox/src/main/java/org/apache/fontbox/type1/Type1Font.jav[0m[1;92ma:42[0m[39m-[0m[1;36m50[0m[39m<[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [35m/[0m[95mcode_range[0m[39m>  [0m                                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   <code_range>fontbox/src/main/java/org/apache/fontbox/type1/Type1Font.jav[0m[1;92ma:67[0m[39m-[0m[1;36m90[0m[39m<[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [35m/[0m[95mcode_range[0m[39m>  [0m                                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   <code_range>fontbox/src/main/java/org/apache/fontbox/type1/Type1Parser.jav[0m[1;92ma:540[0m[39m-[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m548[0m[39m<[0m[35m/[0m[95mcode_range[0m[39m>  [0m                                                                  [2m                [0m

[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<[0m[35m/[0m[95mfix_strategy[0m[1m>[0m                                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         ===Evaluation [33mEnd[0m===                                                                [2m                [0m

[2;36m                    [0m         [39mJNI global refs: [0m[1;36m26[0m[39m, weak refs: [0m[1;36m0[0m                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m===Evaluation [0m[33mReport[0m[39m===[0m                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m# Evaluation Report[0m                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## Summary[0m                                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mThe initial issue was a LibFuzzer timeout during fuzz testing of PDF text [0m          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mextraction, with the main thread hanging in Type [0m[1;36m1[0m[39m font parsing [0m                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;39m([0m[39m`Type1Parser.parseBinary` called via [0m                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`TraceDataFlowNativeCallbacks.traceConstCmpInt`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m. To mitigate potential overly [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mlarge or malicious font segments, a patch was proposed that introduced a [0m           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`MAX_BINARY_SEGMENT_SIZE` [0m[1;39m([0m[1;36m5[0m[39m MB[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m constant and added size-check guards in three [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mareas:  [0m                                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- `Type1Font.createWithPFB` and `createWithSegments`  [0m                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- `Type1Parser.parseBinary`  [0m                                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Embedded font handling in `PDType1Font`  [0m                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mAfter applying the patch, the PDFBox module failed to compile with dozens of syntax[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39merrors in `PDType1Font.java`, primarily complaining about stray `try`[0m[35m/[0m[39m`catch` [0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mblocks and misplaced braces.[0m                                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## Description[0m                                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1[0m[39m. Initial issue  [0m                                                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - During a fuzzing session with Jazzer [0m                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;39m([0m[39m`PDFExtractTextFuzzer.fuzzerTestOneInput`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m, the harness timed out after ~[0m[1;36m27[0m[39m s.  [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - The thread dump shows the main thread stuck in the native callback [0m            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`traceConstCmpInt`, deep inside `Type1Parser.parseBinary`, indicating heavy work [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mdecrypting or lexing large Type [0m[1;36m1[0m[39m font data.  [0m                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m2[0m[39m. Key observations  [0m                                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - The hang occurs consistently in the binary parsing path of Type [0m[1;36m1[0m[39m fonts.  [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - No outright crash or exception was thrown—execution simply exceeds the [0m        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mLibFuzzer timeout.  [0m                                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - The code paths involved are in the FontBox module [0m[1;39m([0m[39m`Type1Parser`, `Type1Font`[0m[1;39m)[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mand the PDFBox font loader [0m[1;39m([0m[39m`PDType1Font`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m.  [0m                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m3[0m[39m. Patch attempt  [0m                                                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - A new public constant `Type1Font.MAX_BINARY_SEGMENT_SIZE = 5_000_000` was [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39madded.  [0m                                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - In `[0m[1;35mType1Font.createWithPFB[0m[1;39m([0m[39mbyte[0m[1;39m[[0m[1;39m][0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` and `[0m[1;35mcreateWithSegments[0m[1;39m([0m[39mbyte[0m[1;39m[[0m[1;39m][0m[39m, byte[0m[1;39m[[0m[1;39m][0m[1;39m)[0m[39m`,[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39meach segment’s length is checked against the max; violations throw `IOException`.  [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - In `[0m[1;35mType1Parser.parseBinary[0m[1;39m([0m[39mbyte[0m[1;39m[[0m[1;39m][0m[1;39m)[0m[39m`, inputs larger than the max are rejected [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mbefore decryption.  [0m                                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - In `PDType1Font`, before invoking the Type [0m[1;36m1[0m[39m font parser on embedded PFB or [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mraw segments, the code checks buffer and segment sizes against the same max.  [0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   The intention was to fail early on oversized inputs and avoid the expensive [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mparsing that leads to timeouts.[0m                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m4[0m[39m. Compilation result  [0m                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - The build of the PDFBox module stops with ~[0m[1;36m100[0m[39m errors in `PDType1Font.java`.  [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Error messages include:  [0m                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     • “‘try’ without ‘catch’, ‘finally’ or resource declarations”  [0m                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     • “‘catch’ without ‘try’”  [0m                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     • “illegal start of type” [0m[35m/[0m[39m “identifier expected”  [0m                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - These point to misplaced or mismatched braces and an incorrectly constructed [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`try`[0m[35m/[0m[39m`catch` block around the newly inserted guard code.[0m                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m5[0m[39m. Areas for further investigation  [0m                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - The `PDType1Font` class around the embedded font handling section [0m[1;39m([0m[39mlines [0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m~[0m[1;36m200[0m[39m–[0m[1;36m300[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m where the patch wrapped code in additional `if` blocks. A brace-level [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mmismatch likely broke the surrounding `try` structure.  [0m                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - The precise locations and indentation of the inserted size checks in [0m          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`PDType1Font.java` to ensure they integrate cleanly with existing `try`[0m[35m/[0m[39m`catch` [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mclauses.  [0m                                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Consistency across modules: confirm that the guards in `Type1Font` and [0m        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`Type1Parser` compile and work as intended before reapplying the `PDType1Font` [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mchanges.  [0m                                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mNo root cause diagnosis or alternative solutions are offered; this report strictly [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mdocuments the initial timeout issue, the patch attempt to bound font segment sizes,[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mand the resulting compilation failures.[0m                                             [2m                [0m
