[2;36m                    [0m         [39m          ```java[0m                                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m          if [0m[1;39m([0m[39msegment1.length > MAX_BINARY_SEGMENT_SIZE[0m                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m              || segment2.length > MAX_BINARY_SEGMENT_SIZE[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m[1;39m{[0m                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m              throw new [0m[1;35mIOException[0m[1;39m([0m[32m"Type1 segments too large: "[0m                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m                  + segment1.length + [0m[32m", "[0m[39m + segment2.length[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m          [0m[1;39m}[0m                                                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m          ```[0m                                                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      - In [0m[1;35mcreateWithSegments[0m[1;39m([0m[39mbyte[0m[1;39m[[0m[1;39m][0m[39m segment1, byte[0m[1;39m[[0m[1;39m][0m[39m segment2[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m:[0m                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m        * At the very beginning, insert:[0m                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m          ```java[0m                                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m          if [0m[1;39m([0m[39msegment1.length > MAX_BINARY_SEGMENT_SIZE[0m                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m              || segment2.length > MAX_BINARY_SEGMENT_SIZE[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m[1;39m{[0m                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m              throw new [0m[1;35mIOException[0m[1;39m([0m[32m"Type1 segments too large: "[0m                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m                  + segment1.length + [0m[32m", "[0m[39m + segment2.length[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m          [0m[1;39m}[0m                                                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m          ```[0m                                                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   b. In fontbox/src/main/java/org/apache/fontbox/type1/Type1Parser.java:  [0m         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      - Add import if missing:[0m                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m        ```java[0m                                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m        import org.apache.fontbox.type1.Type1Font;[0m                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m        ```[0m                                                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      - At the top of the private [0m[1;35mparseBinary[0m[1;39m([0m[39mbyte[0m[1;39m[[0m[1;39m][0m[39m bytes[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m method, before any [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mdecryption, insert:[0m                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m        ```java[0m                                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m        if [0m[1;39m([0m[39mbytes.length > Type1Font.MAX_BINARY_SEGMENT_SIZE[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m[1;39m{[0m                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m            throw new [0m[1;35mIOException[0m[1;39m([0m[32m"Type1 binary segment too large: "[0m[39m + [0m             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mbytes.length[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m        [0m[1;39m}[0m                                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m        ```[0m                                                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m2[0m[39m. Correct and reapply embedded‐font guards in PDType1Font.java without altering [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mexisting try/catch structure:[0m                                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   a. In pdfbox/src/main/java/org/apache/pdfbox/pdmodel/font/PDType1Font.java, [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mlocate the `try [0m[1;39m{[0m[39m … [0m[1;39m}[0m[39m` block starting at line ~[0m[1;36m209[0m[39m that reads `byte[0m[1;39m[[0m[1;39m][0m[39m bytes = [0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;35mfontFile.toByteArray[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;`.[0m                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   b. Immediately after the zero‐length check [0m[1;39m([0m[39m`if [0m[1;39m([0m[39mbytes.length == [0m[1;36m0[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m[1;39m{[0m[39m throw … [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;39m}[0m[39m`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m, insert:[0m                                                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      ```java[0m                                                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      if [0m[1;39m([0m[39mbytes.length > Type1Font.MAX_BINARY_SEGMENT_SIZE[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m[1;39m{[0m                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m          throw new [0m[1;35mIOException[0m[1;39m([0m[32m"Embedded Type1 font too large: "[0m[39m + bytes.length[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      [0m[1;39m}[0m                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      ```[0m                                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      This single guard prevents expensive repairs or parsing on oversized data.  [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   c. Keep the existing `length1 = [0m[1;35mrepairLength1[0m[1;39m([0m[33m...[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` and `length2 = [0m              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;35mrepairLength2[0m[1;39m([0m[33m...[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` calls unchanged.[0m                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   d. Remove any duplicate size‐check code that was previously inserted inside the [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`if [0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m([0m[39mbytes[0m[1;39m[[0m[1;36m0[0m[1;39m][0m[39m & [0m[1;36m0xff[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m == PFB_START_MARKER[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` branch. That early check is redundant [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mwith the single guard above.[0m                                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   e. After computing `segment1` and `segment2` in the `else` branch, insert:[0m       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      ```java[0m                                                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      if [0m[1;39m([0m[39msegment1.length > Type1Font.MAX_BINARY_SEGMENT_SIZE[0m                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m          || segment2.length > Type1Font.MAX_BINARY_SEGMENT_SIZE[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m[1;39m{[0m                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m          throw new [0m[1;35mIOException[0m[1;39m([0m[32m"Embedded Type1 segments too large: "[0m               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m              + segment1.length + [0m[32m", "[0m[39m + segment2.length[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      [0m[1;39m}[0m                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      ```[0m                                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      Place this inside the existing `else` but before the `if [0m[1;39m([0m[39mlength1 > [0m[1;36m0[0m[39m && [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mlength2 > [0m[1;36m0[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` block.  [0m                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   f. Ensure no new braces are added around the `try` or `catch` clauses—only [0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39minsert these `if` statements and their bodies. This preserves the original `try [0m[1;39m{[0m[39m …[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;39m}[0m[39m catch [0m[1;39m([0m[39mDamagedFontException[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m[1;39m{[0m[39m … [0m[1;39m}[0m[39m catch [0m[1;39m([0m[39mIOException[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m[1;39m{[0m[39m … [0m[1;39m}[0m[39m` structure and [0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mresolves the “try without catch” and stray‐brace compilation errors.[0m                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m3[0m[39m. Verify that imports remain correct, no harness or test code is modified, and [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mthat all existing exception flows and resource handling are preserved.  [0m            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m4[0m[39m. Rationale and side‐effect mitigation:[0m                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - A single upstream guard on `bytes.length` ensures that full‐PFB and [0m           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mtwo‐segment PFBs are both bounded, eliminating expensive repair and parsing on [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mover‐large inputs, thus preventing the LibFuzzer timeout.[0m                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Segment‐level checks in Type1Font ensure that standalone API usages of PFB or [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39msegment‐parsing are likewise protected.[0m                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - The MAX_BINARY_SEGMENT_SIZE constant is only in the font parsing modules and [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mdoes not affect other FontBox functions.[0m                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - By not touching the `try`[0m[35m/[0m[39m`catch` structure or harness code, we avoid [0m         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mintroducing new syntax errors or altering fuzzer semantics.[0m                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - This approach centralizes size bounds at the earliest possible point, [0m         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mmaintains existing font‐repair and fallback logic, and ensures compilation succeeds[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mcleanly.[0m                                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<[0m[35m/[0m[95mfix_strategy[0m[1m>[0m                                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         ===Evaluation [33mEnd[0m===                                                                [2m                [0m

[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m===Evaluation [0m[33mReport[0m[39m===[0m                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m# Evaluation Report[0m                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## Summary[0m                                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mAn automated fuzzing run of PDFBox’s Type [0m[1;36m1[0m[39m font support ended in a libFuzzer [0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mtimeout while parsing a PFB font. The fuzzer hung in `Type1Parser.parseBinary`, [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mlikely due to processing a large or malformed input. A patch was applied to [0m        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mintroduce a maximum allowed segment size [0m[1;39m([0m[1;36m5[0m[39m MB[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m and guard checks in `Type1Font`, [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`Type1Parser`, and `PDType1Font`. After applying the patch, the PDFBox compilation [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mfailed with dozens of syntax errors in `PDType1Font.java` [0m[1;39m([0m[39me.g., “try without [0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mcatch,” “catch without try,” missing identifiers, illegal start of type, etc.[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m.[0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## Description[0m                                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mInitial Issue  [0m                                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- The fuzzer run reported “ERROR: libFuzzer: timeout” after ~[0m[1;36m27[0m[39m s of execution.  [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- The main thread was stuck in a native callback [0m                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`TraceDataFlowNativeCallbacks.traceConstCmpInt`, with a stack trace descending into[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`[0m[1;35mType1Parser.parseBinary[0m[1;39m([0m[33m...[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m`, then through PDFBox’s font and text‐stripping logic[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39minvoked by the fuzz harness.  [0m                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- No explicit exception or crash was thrown; rather, the parser never returned, [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mtriggering the timeout.  [0m                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mImportant Observations  [0m                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Parsing happens in two binary segments [0m[1;39m([0m[39mPFB segment1 and segment2[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m.  [0m             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- The fuzzer likely generated an input with excessively large or pathological [0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mbinary segments, causing the parser to spend excessive time or resources.  [0m         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- The timeout points to `Type1Parser.parseBinary`, before any document‐level PDF [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39moperations.  [0m                                                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mPatch Attempt  [0m                                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1[0m[39m. Introduced a constant `Type1Font.MAX_BINARY_SEGMENT_SIZE = 5_000_000`.  [0m         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m2[0m[39m. In `[0m[1;35mType1Font.createWithPFB[0m[1;39m([0m[39mbyte[0m[1;39m[[0m[1;39m][0m[39m pfbBytes[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m`:[0m                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Throw `IOException` if `pfbBytes.length` exceeds the limit.  [0m                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - After parsing PFB headers, guard `segment1` and `segment2` lengths.  [0m          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Call `[0m[1;35mparser.parse[0m[1;39m([0m[39msegment1, segment2[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m`.  [0m                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m3[0m[39m. In `[0m[1;35mType1Font.createWithSegments[0m[1;39m([0m[39mbyte[0m[1;39m[[0m[1;39m][0m[39m, byte[0m[1;39m[[0m[1;39m][0m[1;39m)[0m[39m`:[0m                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Guard each segment length before invoking `Type1Parser.parse`.  [0m               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m4[0m[39m. In `[0m[1;35mType1Parser.parseBinary[0m[1;39m([0m[39mbyte[0m[1;39m[[0m[1;39m][0m[39m bytes[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m`:[0m                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Prepend a length guard check against `Type1Font.MAX_BINARY_SEGMENT_SIZE`.  [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Proceed to decrypt and lex if within bounds.  [0m                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m5[0m[39m. In `PDType1Font` [0m[1;39m([0m[39mPDFBox module[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m:[0m                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Around embedded PFB font stream handling, add checks on `bytes.length`.  [0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - After splitting into `segment1` and `segment2`, guard each segment’s size [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mbefore calling `Type1Font.createWithSegments`.[0m                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mPatch Result [0m[35m/[0m[39m Build Output  [0m                                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- The added guards in FontBox compiled successfully.  [0m                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- PDFBox’s `PDType1Font.java` now emits ~[0m[1;36m100[0m[39m compilation errors. Examples:[0m          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  - “‘try’ without ‘catch’, ‘finally’ or resource declarations”  [0m                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  - “‘catch’ without ‘try’”  [0m                                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  - “identifier expected”  [0m                                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  - “illegal start of type”  [0m                                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  - “class, interface, or enum expected”  [0m                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- The errors indicate misplaced or mismatched braces around the newly inserted [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mguard logic, breaking the method structure.  [0m                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mAreas for Further Investigation  [0m                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Inspect `PDType1Font.java` in the region handling embedded Type [0m[1;36m1[0m[39m streams:[0m        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  - Verify that `try [0m[1;39m{[0m[39m … [0m[1;39m}[0m[39m catch` blocks remain syntactically correct after [0m        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39minserting size checks.  [0m                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  - Confirm matching braces and indentation around the inserted `if [0m[1;39m([0m[39mbytes.length >[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m…[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m[1;39m{[0m[39m throw … [0m[1;39m}[0m[39m` and subsequent code.  [0m                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Review related methods in `PDType1Font` to ensure no extraneous or missing [0m       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39msemicolons/braces were introduced.  [0m                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Examine any code generation or formatting rules in the PDFBox build to understand[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mwhy the patch disrupted block boundaries.  [0m                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Validate consistency of imports and class references after adding [0m                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`Type1Font.MAX_BINARY_SEGMENT_SIZE` usage in PDFBox.[0m                                [2m                [0m

[2;36m                    [0m         [39mpdfbox/src/main/java/org/apache/pdfbox/pdmodel/font/PDType1Font.jav[0m[1;92ma:214[0m[39m-[0m[1;36m221[0m        [2m                [0m

[2;36m                    [0m         [39mpdfbox/src/main/java/org/apache/pdfbox/pdmodel/font/PDType1Font.jav[0m[1;92ma:237[0m[39m-[0m[1;36m245[0m        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m```[0m                                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m237[0m[39m:                        byte[0m[1;39m[[0m[1;39m][0m[39m segment1 = [0m[1;35mArrays.copyOfRange[0m[1;39m([0m[39mbytes, [0m[1;36m0[0m[39m, [0m         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mlength1[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m238[0m[39m:                        byte[0m[1;39m[[0m[1;39m][0m[39m segment2 = [0m[1;35mArrays.copyOfRange[0m[1;39m([0m[39mbytes, length1, [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mlength1 + length2[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m239[0m[39m:[0m                                                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m240[0m[39m:                        [0m[35m/[0m[35m/[0m[39m empty streams are simply ignored[0m                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m241[0m[39m:                        if [0m[1;39m([0m[39mlength1 > [0m[1;36m0[0m[39m && length2 > [0m[1;36m0[0m[1;39m)[0m                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m242[0m[39m:                        [0m[1;39m{[0m                                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m243[0m[39m:                            t1 = [0m[1;35mType1Font.createWithSegments[0m[1;39m([0m[39msegment1, [0m        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39msegment2[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m244[0m[39m:                        [0m[1;39m}[0m                                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m245[0m[39m:                    [0m[1;39m}[0m                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m```[0m                                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<[0m[35m/[0m[95mcode[0m[39m>[0m                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<[0m[35m/[0m[95mcode_snippets[0m[39m>[0m                                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## Fix Strategy[0m                                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<fix_strategy>[0m                                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1[0m[39m. Root‐cause Analysis[0m                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - The compilation errors in PDType1Font.java stem from misplaced or extra [0m       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mclosing braces introduced around the newly added size‐guard `if` blocks. These [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mstray braces break the `try [0m[1;39m{[0m[39m … [0m[1;39m}[0m[39m catch [0m[1;39m{[0m[39m … [0m[1;39m}[0m[39m` structure, leading to “try without [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mcatch” and “catch without try” errors.[0m                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - No other files in PDFBox or FontBox report syntax issues; the misbalanced [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mbraces are local to PDType1Font.java in the region handling embedded PFB streams.[0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - The desired logic—rejecting overly large embedded font data or [0m                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39msegments—remains correct, but must be inlined without altering the surrounding [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mblock boundaries.[0m                                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m2[0m[39m. Strategy Overview[0m                                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - In PDType1Font.java, within the `try [0m[1;39m{[0m[39m … [0m[1;39m}[0m[39m` block that reads and splits the [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39membedded font bytes:[0m                                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     a[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m After verifying `bytes.length != [0m[1;36m0[0m[39m`, insert a guard `if [0m[1;39m([0m[39mbytes.length > [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mMAX…[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m throw IOException…;` inside the same block.[0m                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     b[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m In the two‐segment branch [0m[1;39m([0m[39mimmediately after `byte[0m[1;39m[[0m[1;39m][0m[39m segment1 = …` and [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`byte[0m[1;39m[[0m[1;39m][0m[39m segment2 = …`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m, insert a guard `if [0m[1;39m([0m[39msegment1.length > MAX… || [0m              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39msegment2.length > MAX…[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m throw IOException…;`.[0m                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Critically, do NOT introduce any extra `[0m[1;39m{[0m[39m` or `[0m[1;39m}[0m[39m` beyond the `if [0m[1;39m([0m[39m…[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m[1;39m{[0m[39m … [0m[1;39m}[0m[39m` [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mthat would close the outer `try` or `else` prematurely.[0m                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Remove any stray closing brace added by the prior patch. Ensure there is [0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mexactly one closing `[0m[1;39m}[0m[39m` matching each opened block:[0m                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     • One for the `if [0m[1;39m([0m[39mbytes[0m[1;39m[[0m[1;36m0[0m[1;39m][0m[39m==PFB_START_MARKER[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m … else [0m[1;39m{[0m[39m … [0m[1;39m}[0m[39m`[0m                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     • One for the outer `try [0m[1;39m{[0m[39m … [0m[1;39m}[0m[39m` before its `catch`[0m                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Maintain existing catch blocks and imports; do not modify harness, test code, [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mor other PDFBox/FontBox logic.[0m                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m3[0m[39m. Detailed Steps[0m                                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   a[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m Open pdfbox/src/main/java/org/apache/pdfbox/pdmodel/font/PDType1Font.java.[0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   b[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m Locate the `try [0m[1;39m{[0m[39m` block starting at line ~[0m[1;36m209[0m[39m.[0m                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   c[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m Immediately after the `if [0m[1;39m([0m[39mbytes.length == [0m[1;36m0[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m[1;39m{[0m[39m throw … [0m[1;39m}[0m[39m` check, add:[0m        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      ```[0m                                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      [0m[35m/[0m[35m/[0m[39m guard against overly large embedded font data[0m                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      if [0m[1;39m([0m[39mbytes.length > Type1Font.MAX_BINARY_SEGMENT_SIZE[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m[1;39m{[0m                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m          throw new [0m[1;35mIOException[0m[1;39m([0m[32m"Embedded Type1 font too large: "[0m[39m + bytes.length[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      [0m[1;39m}[0m                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      ```[0m                                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   d[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m Find the two‐segment branch:[0m                                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      ```[0m                                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      byte[0m[1;39m[[0m[1;39m][0m[39m segment1 = [0m[1;35mArrays.copyOfRange[0m[1;39m([0m[33m...[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      byte[0m[1;39m[[0m[1;39m][0m[39m segment2 = [0m[1;35mArrays.copyOfRange[0m[1;39m([0m[33m...[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      ```[0m                                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      Directly afterward, insert:[0m                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      ```[0m                                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      [0m[35m/[0m[35m/[0m[39m guard against overly large embedded PFB segments[0m                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      if [0m[1;39m([0m[39msegment1.length > Type1Font.MAX_BINARY_SEGMENT_SIZE[0m                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m          || segment2.length > Type1Font.MAX_BINARY_SEGMENT_SIZE[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m[1;39m{[0m                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m          throw new [0m[1;35mIOException[0m[1;39m([0m[32m"Embedded Type1 segments too large: "[0m               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m              + segment1.length + [0m[32m", "[0m[39m + segment2.length[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      [0m[1;39m}[0m                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      ```[0m                                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   e[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m Remove the extra `[0m[1;39m}[0m[39m` that followed the original `t1 = [0m                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;35mType1Font.createWithSegments[0m[1;39m([0m[33m...[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` in the last patch. After insertion, the [0m         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mstructure should be:[0m                                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      ```[0m                                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      if [0m[1;39m([0m[39mlength1>[0m[1;36m0[0m[39m && length2>[0m[1;36m0[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m[1;39m{[0m                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m          [0m[35m/[0m[35m/[0m[39m [0m[1;39m[[0m[39msegment‐size guard[0m[1;39m][0m                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m          [0m[35m/[0m[35m/[0m[39m [0m[1;39m[[0m[39mexisting t1 assignment[0m[1;39m][0m                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      [0m[1;39m}[0m                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      ```[0m                                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   f[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m Verify balanced braces:[0m                                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      - The `else [0m[1;39m{[0m[39m … [0m[1;39m}[0m[39m` that contains the two‐segment logic has its opening and [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mclosing braces.[0m                                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      - The `try [0m[1;39m{[0m[39m … [0m[1;39m}[0m[39m` block remains intact and is followed by its `catch` [0m        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mclauses.[0m                                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   g[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m Confirm `import org.apache.fontbox.type1.Type1Font;` remains at the top.[0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   h[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m Rebuild PDFBox. All syntax errors in PDType1Font.java should be resolved, and[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mthe fuzzer’s timeout protected by the size guards.[0m                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m4[0m[39m. Justification[0m                                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - This approach preserves the existing `try/catch` flow, only inlining two `if` [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mguards with their own braces. No outer block is closed or opened inadvertently.[0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - It enforces the previously intended maximum segment size without altering [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mharness or parser code structure beyond syntactically safe spots.[0m                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Existing tests and functionality are unaffected, aside from rejecting [0m         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mpathological inputs earlier with `IOException`.[0m                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Similar guard patterns already compile successfully in Type1Font and [0m          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mType1Parser; here we apply the same pattern with correct braces.[0m                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m5[0m[39m. Potential Side Effects & Mitigations[0m                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Legitimate large embedded Type1 fonts [0m[1;39m([0m[39m>[0m[1;36m5[0m[39m MB[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m will now throw an `IOException`.[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mIf a real use case needs larger segments, the constant could be configured, but [0m[1;36m5[0m[39m [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mMB is chosen to curb fuzzing hangs.[0m                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - No other exceptions or catch blocks are added, so error reporting remains [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mconsistent.[0m                                                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - A clean code‐format [0m[1;39m([0m[39me.g., Maven formatter[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m should be applied after patching [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mto maintain style conventions.[0m                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m6[0m[39m. File Ranges to Patch[0m                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<code_range>pdfbox/src/main/java/org/apache/pdfbox/pdmodel/font/PDType1Font.jav[0m[1;92ma:21[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;92m4[0m[39m-[0m[1;36m221[0m[39m<[0m[35m/[0m[95mcode_range[0m[39m>[0m                                                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<code_range>pdfbox/src/main/java/org/apache/pdfbox/pdmodel/font/PDType1Font.jav[0m[1;92ma:23[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;92m7[0m[39m-[0m[1;36m245[0m[39m<[0m[35m/[0m[95mcode_range[0m[39m>[0m                                                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<[0m[35m/[0m[95mfix_strategy[0m[1m>[0m                                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         ===Evaluation [33mEnd[0m===                                                                [2m                [0m
